choices.text:
Who was the president of the United States in 1996?
The President of the United States in 1996 was Bill Clinton. He began his second term as President on January 20, 1997 and served until January 20, 2001. During his presidency, Clinton faced many challenges including the impeachment process by the House of Representatives for perjury and obstruction of justice in connection with a sexual harassment lawsuit filed against him by Paula Jones. The Senate acquitted Clinton on both charges on February 12, 1999.
